## üí° Tips for Your Study Approach

Given your **8 years of experience**, I recommend:

- ‚ö° **Skip Phase 1 basics** if you already know them ‚Äî do a self-test with the scenario questions first
- üîÅ **Phases 3 & 4** are most important for senior-level interviews and production systems
- üß™ **Build a mini project** ‚Äî an e-commerce system with Order, Inventory, Payment, and Notification services ‚Äî to apply every concept hands-on
- üìå **Phases 5 & 6** are often underestimated ‚Äî security and observability questions are very common in system design rounds
- üèóÔ∏è Since you use **RabbitMQ + MassTransit**, Phase 3's Saga + Outbox pattern will feel very natural for you

